5 Gifts For People Who Have Everything

We’ve all been there… looking for a gift that will delight that special person in our lives who seems to already have it all, or at least has the bank account to buy it if they wanted to! However, in these cases, the most important thing to remember is that it really is the thought that counts more than the price tag. When a gift comes from the heart, it’s obvious that the giver really cares. We’re here to help, with a selection of gift ideas for the people who seem to have everything.

#1 Sweet Treats

'Nothing is more classic and classy than a gourmet gift. It doesn’t matter who you’re giving it to, the perfect gourmet gift is always a delight!

A Nuttery Signature Chocolate Box

It doesn’t matter how much money you have, you can never have enough chocolate! Our signature chocolate box is full of 36 pieces of Miami Beach milk chocolates. Each chocolate is handmade with only the highest quality ingredients, making for a gourmet, premium chocolate experience. Your giftee will love biting into each flavor and discovering the secret deliciousness inside. If you’re lucky, they might even share! If 36 is too much, they can also be purchased as a 16 or a 9 piece box. But why not go all out?

A Nuttery Specialty Tray

If you want to give a variety of different gourmet sweets, our specialty gift tray may be the perfect choice. Filled with both chocolate praline and peanut butter pops, handpicked Miami Beach truffles, and our best-selling bark, this rustic, wooden sectional tray will last much longer than the delicious choices it holds inside. The even better news is that every treat is Kosher Certified, so they taste good while also being Pareve Kosher.

A Nuttery Signature Roasted Nut Tray

If chocolate isn’t their thing, nuts are an excellent, yet gourmet way to say that you’re “nuts” about them. Our signature roasted nut tray is presented elegantly in our dark, rustic wood tray, and is full of savory, freshly roasted snacks. It comes absolutely packed with salted cashews, Israeli almonds, salted pistachios, and salted peanuts. Paired with a beer or even a fine wine, it’s the gift that keeps on giving (until the snacks run out, of course).

A Gourmet Chocolate & Nut Gift Tray

Can’t decide between giving your giftee chocolate or nuts? Don’t! With our gourmet chocolate and nut gift tray, you don’t have to! Elegantly packaged in our signature rustic wood tray, it’s the perfect gift for someone who can’t decide whether they like salty or sweet more. Individually packaged in quick to grab snacking cups, the tray is full of peanut smoothies, sweet pecans, geshmak, cashew patties, sweet cashews, and salted macadamias. The gift looks so classy they might not want to eat it, but they’ll get over it as soon as they take the first bite.


A Dried Fruit Tray

If that special someone isn’t into chocolate or watches what they eat, there’s also a gourmet gift option for that! Our dried fruit tray is a delicious rainbow of options, just waiting to be enjoyed. Every tray comes with a selection of different dried fruits - pineapple cubes, papaya cubes, kiwi, plums, and peaches. It not only looks beautiful, it’s also healthy! Who said gourmet gifts had to be made out of chocolate? (Pro tip - for the best of both worlds try some chocolate dipped dried pineapple rings or chocolate dipped dried apricots).

Bonus Gift Idea: Baby Shower Gifts!

Not every gift has to be for a holiday or a birthday. Other than diapers and a few things off their gift registry, baby shower gifts are a great way to share the excitement while also sharing a tasty treat. You can even choose to do a gender reveal in the sweetest way possible… with a snack box made out of pink or blue treats! Guests will love it, and you’ll be the hit of the party. When your giftee already has all of the baby supplies they need, tasty treats will always be appreciated.

#2: Something Personalized

If you’ve looked everywhere and can’t seem to find something that fits the person you’re buying for--likely because they seem to already have everything you’ve looked at--that could be because it just hasn’t been made yet! There are an endless amount of personalized companies out there, from Shutterfly to Vistaprint to Etsy. Take some time to think about what your giftee does every day, and what they’d likely use the most. Once you’ve figured that out, go out and get them a personalized version of it! A few personalized gift ideas include monogrammed fancy pens, photo-front notebooks, and notepads with their initials on them. They’ll love how much thought you’ve put into it, and they’ll think of you every time they use it. One of our favorite ideas is a coffee mug with a picture of both of you, filled with dark chocolate covered espresso beans. Any coffee lover will love that daily reminder of how much thought you put into giving them a gift, especially when combined with a tasty, caffeinated gourmet treat.


#3: An Experience

Sometimes the right gift just isn’t out there, because your giftee really isn’t looking for a gift at all! Often, it’s an experience that they’ll remember forever. Whether you give them a new experience that they can do solo, or choose to join them as they do it, even someone who seems to have it all will love doing something they’ve never done before. That could be a class where they learn something new (cooking, leather making, yoga) or going on an adventure (like a beginner’s kayaking trip). They’ll love the thought you’ve put into it, and they’ll likely love it even more if you join them! The best part of giving an experience that the two of you can do together is the ability to broaden both of your horizons. Try a new cuisine together, try stand up paddleboarding, or plan a local brewery tour. The most important gift is actually the time that you spend together, and the memories that you’ll make doing it. You don’t have to be able to hold a gift in your hand for it to be memorable.

#4: A Subscription Service

Sometimes the perfect gift isn’t a single gift, it’s a subscription! There is, quite literally, a subscription service for everyone. It’s just a matter of determining what your special person would enjoy the most! From weekly coffee subscriptions to monthly cigar subscriptions and even subscription boxes for pets, consider paying ahead a few months so that the gift can keep on giving even after that first box is opened. Take some time and think about what you see your giftee enjoying on a regular basis. Are they really into makeup? Try a beauty box! Super into gardening? There’s a seasonal box for those with a green thumb! There’s even a box for cat ladies. If you want to be extra stealthy, don’t tell them that you’ve purchased multiple months and wait for those surprised text messages to start rolling in!

#5: A Self-Care Treat

People of all ages will never be able to turn down the gift of rest and relaxation. Giving them a self-care based treat is the perfect way to say you care about them enough to give them their “me time.” How you choose to pamper your loved one is up to what they like to do for relaxation. For some, this means giving them the gift of a spa day or even just a mani/pedi. For others, it’s a gift basket full of things they can enjoy at home, like a bottle of whisky and a portable massager. Supplies for a nice, relaxing bath are also great, including bath bombs and scrubs, bubble bath, and a nice bottle of wine. No matter what you choose, catering your gift to your giftee will show them just how much you love and appreciate them, and the thought you put into making sure they are rested and relaxed. Throwing a few sweets into any self-care package is never a bad idea, either! Consider a Signature Chocolate Truffle Box, some chocolate pops, or any of our other chocolate gift boxes. All are sure to please even the person who has it all, and everyone appreciates a good box of chocolate.

In Closing

No matter who you’re buying for, giving a gift with thought behind it beats spending a ton of money every time. If you’re looking for a gift for a person who already seems to have everything, focus more on giving them a gift customized to what they’re into instead of trying to out-purchase the other people in their lives. They’ll appreciate the love and care you put into making their special day even more special!
